### Product API Tests

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@productId = 99fd045f-fa9f-4492-957d-e84b6be6c7d5

### 1. Create Product
POST {{baseUrl}}/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Notebook Dell g15",
  "description": "Notebook Dell Inspiron 15 3000",
  "price": 2500.99,
  "stock": 10
}

### 2. Create Product - Invalid Data (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "description": "Produto sem nome",
  "price": -100,
  "stock": -5
}

### 3. Create Product - Duplicate Name (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Notebook Dell",
  "description": "Outro notebook Dell",
  "price": 3000.00,
  "stock": 5
}

### 4. Get All Products (all including inactive)
GET {{baseUrl}}/products

### 5. Get Active Products Only
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?status=active

### 6. Get Inactive Products Only  
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?status=inactive

### 5. Get Product by ID
# @name get_product
GET {{baseUrl}}/products/{{productId}}

### 6. Get Product by Invalid ID (should fail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/products/invalid-id

### 7. Update Product
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/products/{{productId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Notebook Dell Atualizado",
  "description": "Notebook Dell Inspiron 15 3000 - Atualizado",
  "price": 2700.00,
  "stock": 15
}

### 8. Update Product - Partial Update
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/products/{{productId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "price": 2800.00,
  "active": false
}

### 9. Update Product - Invalid Data (should fail)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/products/{{productId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "price": -50,
  "stock": -10
}

### 10. Delete Product
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/products/{{productId}}

### 11. Try to get deleted product (should fail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/products/{{productId}}

